  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to UNICEF Mothers@Work programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UN agency to UN agency contribution agreement from UNICEF to ILO to support salaries and travel costs of 2 Better Work enterprise advisors to implement activities in factories enrolled in the Mothers@Work programme. Key activities include, among other things: &#x2022; Manage the roll out of the Mothers@Work programme; &#x2022; Provide enterprise level consultancy services to improve enterprise performance; &#x2022; Orient other Enterprise Advisor colleagues to assess the implementation of 7 minimum standards in the RMG factories; &#x2022; Select and adapt and contextualise Better Work and Mothers@Work products for use at the individual enterprise level based on needs; &#x2022; Provide technical advice and input into the development of BW and M@W research, products and strategies; &#x2022; Support factories to develop functioning Participation and Safety Committees and to develop their self-improvement plan; &#x2022; Support capacity building of enterprises to implement Mothers@Work; &#x2022; Facilitate Mother at Work enrolment seminars as well as advocacy meetings and workshops with international brands; &#x2022; Collaborate with the technical support consortium team (TSC); &#x2022; Etc.</narrative>
  </description>
